column2: Lake is clear- Packers Bay is murky.
Disc was no longer visible through weeds.  Very windy.
Weeds too thick at 5 feet to see disc any lower.  Weed cutter cutting weeds.
Calm + sunny.  No weed cutting today.  Weeds thick at 5 feet.
Water not as clear.  A lot of suspended particles.
Cleared up since last reading.  Still weedy.  Not as warm
Weeds very thick- couldn't see secchi below 5'- water very clear- and saw lots of fish.
Weeds very thick and some weed cutting going on.
A lot of weeds- not much weed cutting this summer- and the water is clear.
Water is clear- lost sigh of disc in weeds.
Water is clear- too many weeds to see any deeper.
The secchi disc made a break for freedom- left the rope and headed for the bottom.
Water is very clear and the weeds are dying.
Water cloudy- weeds growing up fast.
Water clear. Less weeds than previous years.
Water very clear. Weeds not too bad.
Water getting a little murky- but not bad. More weeds.
Water back to clear. Weeds not too bad.
lost sight of disc in the weeds- water is very clear.
Sunny day- measured in Hood's Bay.
sunny day- weedy- just lost site at bottom-Hoods Bay.
DEEP SPOT- NEAR BOTTOM - 3 LITER VAN DORN
DEEP SPOT- NEAR SURFACE - 3 LITER VAN DORN
Mainly sunny- disk just hit bottom- lost in weeds at bottom
Not as clear.  The cutter was running and stirred up the loake.
Lost in weeds just at bottom.  Suinny.  Water clear and looks good.
Sunny- lake looks good.  Water some grren witht he brown.
Water quality not quite as good.  Not a clear.  Speed boats on the lake.  Partly cloudy- level low.
Disk hit bottom- lost in weeds at bottom.  Lake looks good and clear.
Sunny day.  Lake looked good.  Some what weedy.  Water clear.
Sunny day- the lake look good.  Weedy.  The weed cutter had been down for a couple of days.  Lost the disk in the weeds.  The water was clear all the way down.
Training on data collection for O2 and temp.  O2 taken from packers bay.
Weather clear- sunny- lake looks good- fairly weedy as ussual.  Water clear
Sunny- clear day- lake looks good- a little low.
Weather clear- sunny- mid 70's  nice daty.  Lake level is low.

Sunny- some clouds but sun strong.  Warm.  Lake level was high- there had been flooding and a lot of inflow into the lake. The lake was weedy.  The conveyor had been broken and cutting could not be done.

There had been quite a biit of rain and runnoff.  The weather was clear- sunny.  When swimming noted that there was a lot of silt in the water that clung to the skin.  The water was dark in color and somewhat murky.  The weeds were not bad- had not reached the surface.  Contacted DNR- many lakes in the area reported reduced weeds.  Due to runoff from nearby farms and turbidity in teh lake filtering the sunlight.

Sunny.  The lake looked better.  The level was back to normal.  The rainfall was normal- there had not been any for several days.  The lake looked clearer- when swimming did not notice the silt.  Color not quite as dark.
Measurement just before lakeshore weed treatment.
Sunny day- little wind- minimal weeds in the lake
Mainly sunny- little to no wind.  The lake looked good.  The water was very clear.  The weed load seemed to be less than usual.
Lake was exceptionally clear.  Could see the disk all the way to the bottom. Lake looked could.  The weeds seemed to be not bad at all.
nny day- lake clear.  Could see sechi all the way to the bottom..  Color light brown.  Lake looked good.  GPS - N43D 45.800 min W89D 89.22761 min

Partly sunny- the lake was good.  The color was a light brown but real light.  2 - 3 feet it appeared clear.  Could see the disk to the bottom.  The air temperature was 66.2 There were some more weeds but the weeds were not bad.
Weather clear- the lake looked good.  Clear view to the bottom.  The color was a light yellow.
Partly cloudy - some sun- nice day.  Water a little less clear at this site.
Weather was good- phosphourus and clorophyl samples also taken
Additional helpers:  Geoff Iverson and Joyce Portz
Very windy with mostly sunny skies.  Many cranes in the area.  Very weedy at the bottom and struggled to find a spot to test because of the many weeds.
